1066086170285662208.text: When you fall inevitably, remember you’re that little fledging and you’re literally born for this shit

1066085971794378752.text: You can’t game life like that. No matter what your fears might try to justify. There are no shortcuts or guarantees. So put that stupid harness away and stop torturing yourself with irrational fears - enjoy the moments of peaceful soaring or an exciting ascension

1066085537021231104.text: We’re all fledglings in free fall from time to time, but we all have the natural ability to fly. This is life, you can’t learn to fly without falling. Our mental world doesn’t follow the rules of the physical world however. Not flying too high won’t save you from falling too deep

1066085207441174528.text: It doesn’t matter how high or low you keep your expectations - at any moment life can send you tumbling down. And I don’t even believe in a “rock bottom” to save you from falling further in to the abyss. Because it’s all relative, and it’s all inevitable, and it’s so natural.

1066085043838214145.text: But that fear is irrational, and by trying to put a harness of fear on your dreams like that, you just create inner conflict that turns those dreams in to anxious nightmares. We should just let our heart run free and enjoy the ride. Because guess what, life ain’t fair.

1066084829790269440.text: Worrying about stuff you cannot control is pointless. Fear of falling has got us struggling to harness our hopes and dreams lest they’d rise too high. We’re afraid of falling too deep and hurting ourselves if anything would go wrong.
